article.description: Pat Andree had 24 points, Jordan Cohen added a career-high 21 and Lehigh snapped Bucknell's 10-game win streak 92-89 in overtime on Monday night.
article.headline: Lehigh snaps Bucknell's 10-game winning streak 92-89 in OT
article.linkText: Lehigh snaps Bucknell's 10-game winning streak 92-89 in OT
article.story: BETHLEHEM, Pa. -- Pat Andree had 24 points, Jordan Cohen added a career-high 21 and Lehigh snapped Bucknell's 10-game win streak 92-89 in overtime on Monday night. Kahron Ross scored four straight in the extra period to push Lehigh's lead to 86-81 with 1:26 left and the Mountain Hawks (11-13, 6-7 Patriot League) led again by five at 88-83, but the Bison (17-9, 11-2) hit two 3s in the final 14 seconds to set up a 3-point attempt at the buzzer that would have tied it. Lance Tejada, who finished with 17 points, sank a pair of 3s in overtime -- his second made it 82-79 and gave the Mountain Hawks the lead for good with 2:37 left. Zach Thomas finished two shy of his career high with 36 points and grabbed 13 rebounds for Bucknell, which maintains a 2 1/2-game lead in the conference standings. Bucknell led 69-61 after a 10-0 run in the second half. Lehigh rallied with a 12-3 run to go in front at 73-72. There were four lead changes and three ties in the final 2:14 of regulation.
